01:09.000 --> 01:18.000
This last session deals with the historic Apollo 13 mission and it features four of the flight controllers who successfully brought the astronauts home.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
We're going to follow this with a question and answer session.

01:21.000 --> 01:25.000
I may introduce them in order from my right on on across.

01:25.000 --> 01:27.000
First is Gene Cranff.

01:27.000 --> 01:30.000
Gene holds a degree in aeronautical engineering.

01:30.000 --> 01:35.000
Prior to coming to NASA, he worked as a flight loads test engineer at McDonald Aircraft.

01:35.000 --> 01:41.000
He served as a pilot in the Air Force and he worked as a flight test engineer at Holliman Air Force Base.

01:41.000 --> 01:48.000
He joined NASA in 1960 and worked as a flight director in both the Mercury and Gemini programs.

01:48.000 --> 01:58.000
As a flight director for the Apollo and the Skylab programs, he led the team in mission control during the first lunar landing and the successful return of the Apollo 13 crew.

01:58.000 --> 02:06.000
During the shuttle area era, Gene served as a deputy director of flight operations and the director of mission operations.

02:06.000 --> 02:09.000
