02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
Jerry Griffin.

02:11.000 --> 02:23.000
Jerry Griffin holds a degree in aeronautical engineering.

02:23.000 --> 02:31.000
Prior to coming to NASA, he served as an officer in the Air Force and he worked as an aerospace engineer with the Douglas Aircraft company.

02:31.000 --> 02:40.000
He joined NASA in 1964 and he worked as a flight controller for all of the Gemini flights and as a flight director for all of the 11 Apollo missions.

02:40.000 --> 02:57.000
His positions at NASA included assistant administrator for legislative affairs, deputy associate administrator for man space flight, deputy director of the Dryden Flight Research Center, associate administrator for external relations, and deputy director of the Kennedy Space Center.

